summary: Sure @taylorswift is an absolute legend and icon, but more than that, she is so down to earth. I feel as though I could easily...
body: Sure @taylorswift is an absolute legend and icon, but more than that, she is so down to earth. I feel as though I could easily be her friend and not even mind her status. She’s so funny, sweet, and caring. I’d honestly love to play with her cats, listen to her playing on the piano while writing a new song, and make dinner with her. She’s just one of those rare people that I look at and think, what a wholesome person who anyone would be lucky to call their friend.

tags: look what you made me do
body:
HAPPY 1 YEAR REP TOUR

Happy 1 year Rep!!! This album means the world to me, it showed me that no matter what people have said about you, called you, or spread about you that the only opinions that matter are your own and that your true friends will see that! At the time this album was released I was going through some mature bullying and I had no friends but I would blast “this is why we can have nice things” and “look what you made me do” (and countless other songs) and walk down the hall with my head tall even if I didnt feel that way! Those two songs are such badass songs and even when im not feeling good about myself I can blast those songs are realize that those kids who picked on me dont have anything on me!!! Also I did something bad…DONT EVEN GET ME STARTED UGHHHHHH ANOTHER AMAZING SONG LIKE WHST!!! IF A MAN TALKS SHIT THEN I OWE HIM NOTHING PERIODT!!!!!!! @taylorswift @taylornation

summary: can we talk about the Dixie Chicks Easter egg? Obviously Taylor loved them when she was a kid and they are cool chicks so they...
body: can we talk about the Dixie Chicks Easter egg? Obviously Taylor loved them when she was a kid and they are cool chicks so they fit with the lyric and all that, but there has to be more right? Don’t forget that these women were one of the biggest country acts in the world when they were ostracised and effectively silenced by the country music community because they dared to criticise George Bush and his involvement in the Iraq war, they were told to “shut up and sing” because they were women and no one wanted to hear their opinions on politics or anything else…their careers were almost destroyed because they dared to speak their mind. So, I don’t think the only reason they were included in the mv is because they are cool chicks. especially when Taylor was becoming more politically outspoken during the time she was recording this album, an album that she has already said is more introspective and if their Easter egg is there to represent a song on TS7 about Taylor finding her voice and the internal struggles surrounding that then I am totally here for that.
